content: I don't have access to the specific data of how competitive it is to get accepted into the various study abroad programs at the university of tokyo. however, admission to study abroad programs will usually depend on factors such as the number of seats available, the number of applicants, and the qualifications of the applicants. the application process may require transcripts, letters of recommendation, language proficiency tests, and personal statements, among other things. it is important to carefully review the requirements and deadlines for each program and ensure that the application materials are submitted on time and meet the necessary criteria. additionally, having a strong academic background and relevant experiences can increase the chances of acceptance into the program.
